enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve checking and manipulating the state of the iterator, particularly the 'slotFilled' and 'exhausted' flags.
Both methods interact with the 'slot' and 'slotFilled' variables, although 'element()' throws an exception when the iterator is exhausted.

The 'next()' method relies on the 'hasNext()' method to determine if it should throw a 'NoSuchElementException'. This relationship can be used to construct assertions about the state of the iterator after calling 'next()'.
The 'next()' method returns the same element that 'peek()' would have returned before advancing the iterator. This can be used to construct assertions about the element returned by 'next()'.
